item.caption: MH Confidential Note (Mental Health) - EUNMEE ANNIE LEE MD - 08/13/2012 4:08 PM PDT
item.paragraph:
Formatting of this note might be different from the original.
MEDICATION FOLLOW-UP
CHIEF COMPLAINT:
Manav Agarwal is a 26 Y male, returns for medication management.
UPDATED CLINICAL STATUS/MED RESPONSE:
Tired, feels crash afterward with the ritalin. Inc heart rate and anxiety at night - it's a difft feeling than before the ritalin. Just feels is physically related to the ritalin. Thinks had small boost in the conc/focus arena but not very dramatic. At this point, just wants to try alternative. Not exactly sure now what the lexapro is doing for him - would be interested in trying dec dose in future.
OBJECTIVE:
Psychiatric Medications:
Ritalin 10mg - 2 bid
lexapro 20mg/day
Ativan 1mg 1/2 - 1 bid prn anxiety - prn rarely
Side Effects: see above
Labs/Tests: n/a
Medical Problems: none
Allergies: Celexa
Current Other RX Medications: none
OTC/Alternative/Herbal: mvi, fish oil, melatonin prn sleep
Any updated D&A issues? etoh - socially occ, every other wk. No drugs. Caffeine - about 1 c coffee/day.
Updated MSE: Same. Groomed/neat, casual dress. Pleasant and cooperative. Normal speech and behavior. Mood is down at times, anxious. Affect is mildly anxious, pleasant, even. Logical.
PHQ9: 11
Updated Risk Assessment:
Suicide: denies
Homicide: no risk
DIAGNOSIS:
Axis I: Anxiety d/o nos
Adhd - inattentive
Axis II: Defer
Axis V: 61 - 70 mild symptoms
ASSESSMENT/INTERVENTION/PLAN:
Ritalin not that helpful and side effect, wants to try alternative.
Try adderall 10mg 1/2 - 1 bid.
Continue lexapro 20mg/day for now - discussed re not making too many changes with meds at once so hold off trying dec for now.
Continue Ativan 1mg 1/2 - 1 bid prn anxiety.
Risks and benefits discussed.
Med se reviewed, med ed given, pt ?'s answered.
Informed consent: Yes. Patient consents to treatment with above.
Follow-up appointment: 10/3 430p and pt to contact me in between with update/progress.
Time spent in session: 30mins
Electronically signed by EUNMEE ANNIE LEE MD at 08/13/2012 5:31 PM PDT
